    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The petulance of the Democrats who support Ralph Nader is staggering. Barbara Ehrenreich (Op-Ed, Oct. 26) writes that she ''will be sorry if George Bush defeats Al Gore,'' but if he does, ''don't expect me to be apologetic.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The petulance of the Democrats who support Ralph Nader is staggering. Barbara Ehrenreich (Op-Ed, Oct. 26) writes that she ''will be sorry if George Bush defeats Al Gore,'' but if he does, ''don't expect me to be apologetic.''</p>
        <p>In a race as close as this one,  and the fate of the Supreme Court  at stake, the Naderites' gesture of throwing away their votes is on the level of Roger Clemens's throwing of the splintered bat.</p>
        <p>JANET MALCOLM  New York, Oct. 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
